Delta state Governor, Dr Ifeanyi Okowa and wife, Edith, have tested negative for coronavirus. It will be recalled that the first family was diagnosed with COVID-19 twelve days ago. Okowa’s daughter who tested positive also recovered following 21 days of been quarantined at an isolation centre in the State. Okowa who broke the news Tuesday on his verified Facebook account said that members of his family have all tested negative to the disease. Okowa, who thanked God for his fast recovery, appreciated Deltans for praying for his family’s recovery. Okowa said, “My wife, my daughter and I have tested negative for COVID 19, along with other members of the family. “We give God all praise and wish to appreciate all who have interceded for us in prayers.” He appealed to residents of the state to adhere to the relevant protocols aimed at combating the spread of the virus. He said, “I appeal to all residing in Delta to obey all instructions/ regulations in our collective fight to stop the transmission of the virus. God bless you all”